               <head>History of Bhatner Fort</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Ṣadr Jahān ibn Sayyid Naṣīr al-Dīn Samarqandī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064912 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010109514 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116669" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3748-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled history of the Bhatner Fort (renamed Hanumangadh, Rajasthan) from the period of the Mongol incursions to its award as jāgīr to the family of Mīrzā Sulṭān
</p>
                        <p>Internal reference terms the work as “īn bayāz̤”
</p>
                        <p>The account is incomplete and breaks abruptly without conclusion or colophon
</p>
                        <p>Folios damaged at beginning with substantial loss of text; repaired with gauze
</p>
                        <p>Not dated
</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 27 Oct. 1907
</p>
